<section containing-doc="D.C. Code" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify">
  <num>4-210.14</num>
  <heading>Right to request hearing while absent from District.</heading>
  <text>A recipient shall have the same right to a hearing while absent from the District that he or she had while living in the District.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 4-101" type="History">Apr. 6, 1982, D.C. Law 4-101, § 1014, 29 DCR 1060</annotation>
